---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="How to Analyze nginx Access Log - GigaSieve Guide" description="Step-by-step guide to analyzing nginx access logs for 5xx errors, top IPs, and slow requests.">
    <section class="container mx-auto px-4 py-12 max-w-3xl">
        <nav class="text-sm text-slate-500 mb-6">
            <a href="/guides" class="hover:text-cyan-400">Guides</a>
            <span class="mx-2">/</span>
            <span class="text-slate-400">Analyze nginx Access Log</span>
        </nav>

        <h1 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-slate-200 mb-4">How to Analyze nginx Access Log</h1>
        <p class="text-slate-400 mb-8">
            Your nginx access log contains a wealth of information about traffic, errors, and performance. 
            Here's how to extract insights without installing any tools.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-300 mb-4">Step 1: Get your log file</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-400 mb-6">
            nginx access logs are typically located at <code class="bg-slate-800 px-2 py-1 rounded">/var/log/nginx/access.log</code>. 
            Download a copy to your local machine.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-300 mb-4">Step 2: Open in GigaSieve</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-400 mb-6">
            Drag the file into <a href="/app" class="text-emerald-400 hover:underline">GigaSieve</a>. 
            The app will stream-parse the file and show you lines immediately.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-300 mb-4">Step 3: Find 5xx errors</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-400 mb-6">
            Use the filter: <code class="bg-slate-800 px-2 py-1 rounded">502</code> or <code class="bg-slate-800 px-2 py-1 rounded">504</code>. 
            The Insights panel will show you the distribution of status codes.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-300 mb-4">Step 4: Identify top IPs</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-400 mb-6">
            Check the Top Status Codes panel. If you see many 4xx errors from specific IPs, 
            they might be bots or attackers.
        </p>

        <a href="/app" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-500 to-cyan-500 text-white font-bold py-3 px-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg mb-8">
            Try GigaSieve Now ->
        </a>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-300 mb-4">Related</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <a href="/recipes/logs/nginx-status-codes" class="bg-slate-900 hover:bg-slate-800 rounded-xl p-4 border border-slate-800">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-300">nginx Status Codes Recipe</h3>
            </a>
            <a href="/recipes/logs/top-ips" class="bg-slate-900 hover:bg-slate-800 rounded-xl p-4 border border-slate-800">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-300">Top IPs Recipe</h3>
            </a>
        </div>
    </section>
</Layout>
